      • getDepositionRatePerSite

        public double getDepositionRatePerSite()
        In principle, deposition rate is constant to 0.0035 ML/s. What changes is island density. Consequently, deposition rate in practice varies with the temperature.
        Specified by:
        getDepositionRatePerSite in interface IRates
        Returns:

      • getIslandDensity

        public double getIslandDensity(double temperature)
        Returns the island density mono layer depending on the temperature. These values are taken from many run of multi flake with 200x200 lattice points. The formula to get the number of islands is: N = F^{0.23}·c·(r_tt/F^{1/3})^x Therefore, we can get island density for single flake.
        Specified by:
        getIslandDensity in interface IRates
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        a double density value

      • setDepositionFlux

        public void setDepositionFlux(double diffusionMl)
        Diffusion Mono Layer (F). Utilised to calculate absorption rate. Cox et al. define to be F=0.0035 ML/s. The perimeter deposition is calculated multiplying F (this) and island density.
        Specified by:
        setDepositionFlux in interface IRates
        Parameters:
        diffusionMl - diffusion mono layer (deposition flux)
